html.htmlText:
Welcome to the Sofi Stadium House, Room #1 of the 5 chic bedrooms we offer.

This private room and bathroom with keyless entry pad, is located in a boutique hotel style home, at fraction of the cost of a hotel room.
WALK TO SOFI STADIUM OR FORUM, SAVE $60-100 on PARKING.

CONCIERGE SERVICE AVAILABLE.
To view all of our rooms click on our Airbnb profile.

Location and style, get ready to experience the best that Los Angeles has to offer.
Designed by an HGTV star, Sofi Stadium House was gutted and remodeled by one of top builders in Los Angeles. With its boutique hotel feel, you'll find the house spacious, comfortable and well designed. Enjoy fresh fruit from the citrus orchard, a glass of wine on either of the European style patios, or take a quick walk to Sofi Stadium or the Fabulous Forum. You're very close to LAX, in the center of the city, making it easy to get everywhere.

You're right in the center of LA -Disneyland, Universal Studios, the Getty, Hollywood and Staples center are all less than 30 miles away.

FAQ:

Q: Location?
We are 4 miles east of LAX and the beach, your are right in the middle of the city. It's a few blocks away and walking distance to Sofi Stadium, the Forum and Hollywood Park.
Rent bikes or take an uber to the beach.

Q: Is the neighborhood and house safe?
Inglewood is one of the safest cities in Los Angeles county. They have their own, highly trained (and paid), police force, fire and safety teams. The city has just had billions of dollars invested in the infrastructure and municipal programs. The Sofi Stadium complex is considered to be one of the most important entertainment venues in the world.
The home has a state of the art alarm and monitor system, and there is 24/7 surveillance.

Q. How many rooms are in Sofi Stadium House and how many people are in the home at one time?
There are 5 bedrooms inside the house. The maximum occupancy is 2 guests per room. For the enjoyment of all guests, this policy is strictly enforced and monitored.
All guests may enjoy use of the kitchen, lounge, dining areas and two patios.
There is one private studio that is separate from the house. These guest are welcome to visit either of the two patios.

Q: How do you monitor what is happening in the common areas?
All parking, entrance and common areas are on 24 hour, recorded video. Bedrooms and Bathrooms do not have video monitors.

Q. I don't see a refrigerator in the kitchen. How do I keep my food cold or get ice?
Each room has a personal refrigerator.

Q: How can I see all of your rooms for rent or other listings in Los Angeles?
Click on our Airbnb profile (the round photo) & scroll all the way down to the bottom below the aggregated reviews (on Mobile) or look to the left (on Desktop). You will see all of our other listings.


Q: 1 Night Reservations?
Yes.

Q: Is it comfortable?
Very! Fully equipped kitchen, premium furnishings, updated HVAC, smart TV, Keurig coffee makers. Each room has a smart TV, desk and mini frig/freezer.

Q: Any restaurants close by?
TONS! Some of the best restaurants in Los Angeles are walking distance away at the Sofi Stadium complex or a quick drive to almost endless choices around the city.
Close by are world famous Randy's Donuts, and some of the best soul food restaurants in the country: Lee's Carribbean, Bourbon Street Fish and Dulan's Soul Food Kitchen.



Q: How to book:
A: If you don’t have any questions after reading over the FAQ below then use the instant book. If you send an inquiry we’ll respond promptly, if not immediately.

Q: Why is the price so different for my dates?
A: Airbnb automatically sets our prices based on demand & seasonality. If you don’t search with exact dates Airbnb shows the lowest price throughout the season. Prices range from $65 per night for weekday day-of bookings in January all the way to $350 per night for weekends during peak season summer, events and everywhere in-between.

Q: Heat? Air Conditioning?
The house has a central heating and AC. The temperature is kept at 75. If you like it colder, no problem, the night's in Los Angeles are usually low 70s-high 60s, just open your windows. If you like it warmer when you sleep, each room includes a plush fleece, additional blanket.

Q: Can I check in earlier than 4 or check out later than 11?
We are normally fully booked, which means we need time to make it perfect for a guest like you. This requires our CDC cleaning methods crew the full 5 hours in between guest visits. However you are welcome to leave your packed luggage packed in the room until 3:30 on check out day, and anytime after 11:30 on check in day. After that time, luggage will be stored in the main dining area under the stairs.

Q: Will you reduce your price?
We've been able to provide you with one of the best designed spaces, in a world class location, for the best price in its category. That's why it's always booked. The price is stated on the listing, any changes in price are reflected at the time of booking.

Q: Do you do long-term or monthly rentals?
We will take a longer term renter, which will require a lease after 30 days.


Q: Smoking?
A: On the outside only & please be responsible. Please extinguish and pick up all cigarette butts. There is absolutely no smoking anywhere in the house or studio. If you smoke in the house or studio, you will be charged a $500 cleaning fee to remove the smoke from all the surfaces. Weed is legal in LA, so don't worry about smoking it on the patios. ENJOY!

Q: Do you allow pets?
We love pets, but some of the guests might not, so please leave them at home.
We may be able to be flexible, ask us.

Q: Can we hold events or parties?
A: No.

Q: Can we invite other people who are not registered guests to visit?
No. Please meet your friends and associates at another location.

Q: You charge extra for more than 2 adults, do my kids count?
We do not allow more than 2 guests in any one room at any time.

Q: Parking?

In the back alley, in a lot in back of the house, there are 3 parking spots in the back of the house, first come first serve.

Pull into one of the three spots, with your car facing the tree. Do not block anyone.

If the spots are full or you find it difficult to park, you can unload your bags in the front or the back of the house, and then park overnight across the street on ONLY on W 90th St or on S 8th Ave. Both of these streets are in front of the house.

Do not park overnight in the alley or on any city streets (other than W 90th or S 8th Ave) you will get a ticket. PLEASE READ STREET CLEANING SIGNS TO AVOID A TICKET.



Guest access

You will get an access code to the front and back entrance doors, and your room. You can use this code to access the boat at any time of the day or night during your stay.



It's a shared house, is it noisy?
This house is right in the action, in the middle of the city, under the LAX flight path, on a busy street and it is shared with others. If you're looking for a quiet spot, with no noise, this is not the place for you. We do provide sound machines in each room to help you sleep without noise from guests or the city.

You will get an access code to the front and back entrance doors, and your room. You can use this code to access the boat at any time of the day or night during your stay.

Chic Design
Great Price
California Living
Close to Stadiums, LAX and the Beach

It's a very spacious house with a communal dining area for playing games, enjoying some food, or meeting new friends from around the World. The kitchen has everything you need to prepare and serve a gracious meal. Or you can grab a snack or a cup of tea in the kitchen lounge with it's umber comfy cloud sofa and swivel chair. Step outside, and enjoy a glass of wine or the Los Angeles sunshine in one of two outdoor areas.
When it's time for some privacy, you can slip away to your well appointed, and very private, bed and bath.
You can reach us by text or  the Airbnb site.

The tub in the bathroom is not functional.
Quite time is 10PM-8AM.
Please no loud talking, music or noise during these times.
Only a shower in the bathroom. Tub does not function.
Clean up after yourself in the kitchen, wash the dishes and cookware that you use,
and wipe down the counter. Your other house guests will appreciate that.

content.htmlText: You are blocks away from one of the biggest entertainment centers in the world, Sofi Stadium, the Fabulous Forum and Hollywood Park.  LAX is 4 miles away.   There is a shopping center down the street with all types of shops, Home Depot, Costco, grocery stores, and pretty much anything you need. You are blocks away from one of the biggest entertainment centers in the world, Sofi Stadium, the Fabulous Forum and Hollywood Park.  LAX is 4 miles away.   There is a shopping center down the street with all types of shops, Home Depot, Costco, grocery stores, and pretty much anything you need.  The beach is 4 miles away, a 10 minute car, bike or bus ride.

Inglewood is full of Uber/Lyft drivers and taxis to help you get around if you did not bring or rent a car. If you do have a car parking is free at the back of the property or on the street with a provided permit.

There is also a bus line with a stop on our street, close to the house, that has access to metro/buses anywhere in the city

section.houseRulesSubtitle: You'll be staying in someone's home, so please treat it with care and respect.

html.htmlText:
This is a communal house. 
There are 5 bedrooms with a maximum of two guests in each room. 
Rooms and bathrooms are private.  Kitchen, dining, lounge and outside patios are shared. 
You must clean up after yourself and leave any public area the same way you found it.
Quite time is 10PM-8AM. 
Parties are not allowed.
Guests who are not registered are NOT allowed on the property, inside or out.
There is no smoking inside of the house.  If you smoke, you will be have to pay $500 to have it cleaned by a remediation company.
Each reservation requires a $200 deposit. 
If you damage any linens, furnishings, or any part of the home, without letting us know, your deposit will be used for repairs. 
If you are ok with these rules, please go ahead and book.

section.about:
We are a family who loves to travel the world via AirBnB. So far we've been to 21 countries and counting.  
We have lived in Los Angeles County for over 30 years and love this city. Our favorite spots are the Getty, the beach, the Hollywood Bowl and LACMA Friday night Jazz. 
When we travel you can find us in a luxury vacation rental or high end boutique hotel.  We are very selective about where we stay, it has to be nicer than our home or it's not happening.  We brought that same spirit and special touch to our AirBnBs,  which we consider affordable luxury. We understand the challenges presented to hosts and as a result we are fabulous guests!

features.title: Booking Protection Guarantee
features.subtitle: In the unlikely event a Host needs to cancel your booking within 30 days of check-in, we’ll find you a similar or better home, or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Check-In Guarantee
features.subtitle: If you can’t check into your home and the Host cannot resolve the issue, we’ll find you a similar or better home for the length of your original stay, or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Get-What-You-Booked Guarantee
features.subtitle: If at any time during your stay you find your listing isn't as advertised—for example, the refrigerator stops working and your Host can’t easily fix it, or it has fewer bedrooms than listed—you'll have three days to report it and we’ll find you a similar or better home, or we’ll refund you.

features.subtitle: If you ever feel unsafe, you’ll get priority access to specially-trained safety agents, day or night.
